====================================================================================================
FERMION MASS PRIMES TEST 18
Hierarchy-matched 9 charged-mass null
====================================================================================================
Per-scale joint-structure null. Tests whether the real per-scale
co-occurrence of (within-family sub-percent fits, cross-family fits,
clean chain residuals) is unusual under random plausible hierarchies.

Reading rules (pre-committed, per scale):
  Strong:  fraction matching or exceeding < 0.1%
  Modest:  < 1%
  Weak:    < 5%
  None:    >= 5%

Trials per scale: 1,000,000
Log-span window: real +/- log(2)
Within-family threshold: 1.0%
Cross-family threshold:  3.0%

Selected cross-family ratios: ['t/tau', 't/b', 'c/s']
Scales: 9 common scales (PDG excluded by design)
Candidates generated: 111411 (2^a x p up to 703366)

